# Adab Supabase rules

## Clients

| Client | File | Use |
|--------|------|-----|
| Browser | `createSupabaseBrowserClient()` | Portal/tenant client components |
| Auth (SSR) | `createSupabaseAuthClient()` | Server actions with user session |
| Service | `getSupabaseServerClient()` | Public inserts (inquiries), webhooks |
| Admin mutation | `requireAdminMutationClient()` | Admin write actions |

## Auth roles

- `admin` — CMS, PM panel, brand downloads
- `lister` / portal users — list properties via portal
- `tenant` / `client` — tenant portal, applications

Admin check: JWT metadata `role=admin` OR `profiles.role = admin`.

## Key tables

- `properties` — listings (portal + admin CMS)
- `inquiries` — contact form leads
- `pm_applications` — tenant/PM applications
- `profiles` — user metadata and roles
- `page_views` — first-party analytics

## Patterns

- Always validate input with Zod before insert/update
- Use `revalidatePath` after admin mutations
- Service role for server-side writes that bypass RLS
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client

## SQL migrations

Reference SQL lives in sibling repo `adab-ng-site/supabase/`. Run manually in Supabase SQL Editor — not auto-applied by this app.

## Redirect URLs (production)

- Site URL: `https://adab.ng`
- Callbacks: `https://adab.ng/auth/callback`, `https://adab.ng/portal/verify-email`
